<img width="200" height="212" class="wp-image-302110" style="width: 600px;" src="https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/Kenneth-Okonkwo.jpg" alt=""> Veteran Nigerian actor Kenneth Okonkwo, has resigned his membership of the All Progressive Congress (APC) over its Muslim-Muslim presidential ticket for 2023. The actor made this known on his official Instagram page. He stated that APC’s Muslim-Muslim ticket would permanently destroy the political viability of Christians in the north of Nigeria if allowed to stand. He added that he resigned his membership also in the interest of equity, justice, fairness and peaceful co-existence among Nigerians. (NAN)   FOLLOWING the  nomination of Senator Kassim Shettima, Borno Central, a Muslim as the running mate to the party's  Presidential candidate, Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu, also a Muslim ahead of the 2023 general elections, Senator Ishaku Abbo, APC, Adamawa North has dumped  the Tinubu Support Organisation. In "News" The polity was literary astir, yesterday, as mixed views greeted Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu’s selection of former Governor of Borno State, Senator Kashim Shettima, as his All Progressives Congress, APC running mate for the 2023 presidential election. In "Politics" ...insists it’s ungodly in a multi-religious state Tinubu (left) and Shettima By Peter Duru, Makurdi The Forum of Middle Belt Youth Presidents, FMBYPs, has described the Muslim-Muslim presidential ticket of the All Progressives Congress, APC, as ungodly in a multi-religious state; a slap to the North and an insult on… In "News"